# Orbital and Axial Rotation Model

## Model Scope

This model calculates Earth's motion as a dual-rotational system:
- Spin on its polar axis (daily)
- Orbit around the sun (yearly)

## Equations

Orbital path (simplified):
r(t) = R  
φ(t) = ω_sun * t  
θ(t) = ω_earth * t

Where:
- ω_sun = angular orbital velocity
- ω_earth = axial rotation rate

Total influence = vector sum of ω_sun and ω_earth in space-time

## Application

Used to model:
- Energy field shifts
- Seasonal field compression/dilation
- Solar input and curvature fluctuations
